The paper deals with learning commonsense knowledge from natural language text, which is a common theme in natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques for joint inference over different types of knowledge, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with extracting knowledge from unstructured text, which is a common theme in information retrieval (IR) and computer vision (CV), hence cs.IR and cs.CV are also likely sub-categories.
